# MDAP / MAKER Rules

1. Always decompose tasks into the smallest possible subtasks.
2. Each AI request must handle only ONE microtask.
3. AI must keep solutions under 50 lines unless explicitly allowed.
4. No extra features or assumptions outside the current subtask.
5. Generate 3 candidate solutions for each microtask upon request.
6. If code is long, rambling, or poorly formatted, discard it.
7. Code must pass tests before being accepted.
8. Never modify other modules without explicit instruction.
9. Always expose clear input/output for microtasks.
10. Prefer simple, deterministic solutions.
